1
00:00:03,031 --> 00:00:05,281
At the Hyatt Regency, the deadly change

2
00:00:05,281 --> 00:00:06,617
looked like a shortcut.

3
00:00:07,599 --> 00:00:09,714
The walkway design used one continuous

4
00:00:09,714 --> 00:00:11,760
hanger rod from roof to fourth floor

5
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:13,345
to second floor.

6
00:00:13,345 --> 00:00:14,931
In shop drawings,

7
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,009
it became two shorter rods.

8
00:00:17,009 --> 00:00:18,558
Easier to build.

9
00:00:18,558 --> 00:00:20,107
But the load path

10
00:00:20,107 --> 00:00:21,709
changed.

11
00:00:21,709 --> 00:00:23,310
The fourth-floor connection now

12
00:00:23,310 --> 00:00:25,088
carried both walkways, not one.

13
00:00:25,850 --> 00:00:27,772
The load essentially doubled.

14
00:00:27,888 --> 00:00:31,337
NBS later found the original design was

15
00:00:31,337 --> 00:00:34,786
already weak; the revision left roughly

16
00:00:34,786 --> 00:00:37,921
one-third of code-expected capacity.

17
00:00:37,921 --> 00:00:41,266
On July 17, 1981, two walkways collapsed

18
00:00:41,266 --> 00:00:43,251
during a crowded dance.

19
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:46,700
Official records count 113 dead and 186

20
00:00:46,700 --> 00:00:48,027
injured.

21
00:00:48,027 --> 00:00:49,354
This was not a shop detail.

22
00:00:49,395 --> 00:00:52,207
It was a structural redesign.

23
00:00:53,192 --> 00:00:55,261
Every handoff treated it like paperwork.

24
00:00:55,863 --> 00:00:58,957
Small causes, massive consequences.
